sentences.en: Accordingly, the textual world shaped by language is also indeterminate.

sentences.en: Centrifugals reduce cost to a indeterminate extent by giving a gas virtually free of oil.

sentences.en: Conclusions: Helical CT scanning detects many indeterminate nodules, but few are malignant.

sentences.en: Dr Amid was a man of indeterminate age.

sentences.en: I give indeterminate money to poor men.

sentences.en: I hope to carry on for an indeterminate period.

sentences.en: Such force systems are said to be statically indeterminate.

sentences.en: The clay had hardened, some time in this indeterminate day which had lasted a thousand years.

sentences.en: Then after an indeterminate dark interval , Prissy was beside her, chattering on in a pleased way.

sentences.en: We assume that the sex of the lion is ab initio _ indeterminate.
